I'm pretty disappointed in mi mom. I'd hoped that she had just a little open-mindedness in her. obviously she hasn't. I was talking with her about placebo's brain molko and his bisexuality was mentioned. she was all like: iehl! he's not a bisexual is he? iehlyuckiefuckie! that is gross!...not with those particular words off course but still, she was totally showing her disgust. so I was all like: omg, you didn't just say that! you can't talk that way about bisexuals! jesus!...not with those particular words off course but still, I was showing my unbelief. then my sister came in and actually agreed with me and told mi mom how pathetically she was reacting (which was special 'cause she's pretty homophobic herself). so I was pretty pissed and disappointed. while my sister started to make jokes about bisexuality. I felt soo embarrassed.

I don't think I'll be able to tell'em about me being bisexual...anytime soon. it makes me sad. I really want to be myself for 100% around them, guess that's not possible.  :(

just had teh adventure. *rolls eyes*
so when I came home from walking the dog I found surprisingly enough the door locked. I didn't have the key, for usually the door is never locked. I didn't know what to do 'cause mi mom was still at her work and none of my sisters would come home within at least half an hour. then I found out that the window of my bedroom was open and I figured that I could go through it if I would just climb on the roof. which really isn't as hard and dangerous as it sounds. so I started to climb on a chair and then on the container. from where I had to climb on a wall and from there on the roof. myeahmyeah. but as I was standing on the container I found out that I simple didn't dare. >.< so there I was, standing on the container, in the freezing cold. I decided to step off again, since I couldn't make myself useful standing on it. then the dog started to freak out, for thinking I was a burglar. it just wouldn't stop barking. I started to get pretty aggressive. so I went to the neighbours to call my mom to come home immediately. the sweet/adorable neighbourkid made me happy again though. he's just teh sweetness.

well, that was quite a long story over nothing really. :)
